name: GET IT
description: In August/September 2009, Milton Keynes' very own rock n roll vagabonds LIONSEX recorded their debut album Get It with producer/guitarist/songwriter Matt Bond, whose recent credits include Bullet For My Valentine and Transcend Records new UK rap metallers Idiom, and is mixed by Jeff Rose and Martin Ford, who also worked with Bullet on all three albums as well as SHOGUN by Trivium, and are reknown within the metal circuit for over 20 years, both having been members of UK metal legends Dub War and Skindred. Released on 8th December 2009 on their own indie label Roar Power, Get It was recorded at Matts Rock Farm studio in Cwmbran, Wales, over 10 days and funded on the money made from selling their demos in one compete CD called Demolicious at gigs. It features several songs from Demolicious plus some new additions to the popular live set, such as Rip-Off Britain and Too Good.
